text:
Sorry SL stands for Screen Left (my bad using jargon)

And yeah that’s right with the roto, if you think of it in planes/surfaces you’ll see which bits will be able to track with the same tracker. 

And yeah that’s correct about shape breakdown, it’s so there is less to focus on so you’ll be able to concentrate better on wether it is sliding or not. 

Great news about the render!

Don't apologize, the more jargon I see is probably more beneficial! Haha

Alright thanks for explaining all that, helps a lot!
Hahaha it comes in useful when I’m writing tech notes for the guys in India or Canada rather than having to do a little annotation every time :P

Haha that's fair! 

I've got the first version of the street. There's definitely a number of masks that are bouncing that need fixing, which is a bit disappointing to be honest.
